title: Data Acquisition Engineer Intern
description: Join our dynamic team as a Data Acquisition Engineer Intern. You'll work on developing data collection systems, implementing data pipelines, and analyzing sensor data for our FSAE vehicle. This role offers hands-on experience with real-time data processing and automotive engineering.

title: Aerodynamics Graduate Engineer
description: We're seeking a recent graduate to join our aerodynamics team. You'll be responsible for CFD analysis, wind tunnel testing, and aerodynamic optimization of our race car. This role provides excellent career development opportunities in motorsport engineering.

title: Junior Mechanical Design Engineer
description: Join our mechanical design team as a Junior Engineer. You'll work on chassis design, suspension systems, and component optimization. This role requires 1-2 years of experience in automotive or motorsport engineering.

title: Software Development Intern
description: Exciting opportunity for a software development intern to work on telemetry systems, data visualization tools, and embedded software for our FSAE vehicle. Gain experience in real-time systems and automotive software development.

title: Graduate Electronics Engineer
description: Join our electronics team as a graduate engineer. You'll work on PCB design, sensor integration, and electrical systems for our race car. This role offers comprehensive training in automotive electronics and embedded systems.

title: Junior Manufacturing Engineer
description: We're looking for a Junior Manufacturing Engineer to optimize our production processes, develop jigs and fixtures, and ensure quality control. This role requires experience with CNC machining and composite manufacturing.

title: Business Development Intern
description: Join our business development team as an intern. You'll assist with sponsor relations, marketing campaigns, and event planning. This role provides valuable experience in motorsport business operations and networking.

title: Graduate Project Manager
description: We're seeking a graduate project manager to coordinate our FSAE team activities, manage timelines, and ensure project deliverables. This role offers excellent leadership development opportunities in engineering project management.
